# Absolute base URL (host root, no path) of the PKIS Flask backend. The native
# (Capacitor) build reaches it over the network, so it is NOT same-origin. The
# client appends the '/pkis-api' prefix itself (see src/lib/api.ts).
#
# You normally DON'T need this file — the build target is baked into the npm
# scripts (Vite reads VITE_-prefixed vars from the shell env at build time):
#
#   - `npm run apk`      -> https://pkis.dev   (VPS prod; default)
#   - `npm run apk:dev`  -> http://10.0.2.2:5000   (local backend, Android emulator)
#
# Override here only for a one-off target (e.g. a phone testing against a LAN /
# Tailscale backend). Copy to `.env` and set:
#
#   - Android emulator -> host loopback:   http://10.0.2.2:5000
#   - phone on the LAN / Tailscale:        http://<workstation-ip>:5000
#   - web dev (same-origin via vite proxy): leave UNSET
#
# Cleartext (http://) to LAN/emulator hosts is gated by android's
# network_security_config.xml; prod (https://pkis.dev) needs nothing there.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://10.0.2.2:5000
